column1: Note: Of the gauges included in this folder, only the gauge kept by Vynne & Everett has a stn number. This record does however have a two-decade gap.
I believe that this can be filled with the record named SWAFFHAM: HOMEWOOD (HOLMEWOOD), as this is where Everett (a Corn Merchant) lived. The gauge, for the rest of the time was near the station.
